<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-12T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-12T16:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.113/311: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-12T17:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">July 12,
                                        1928—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>62. Department’s telegram No. 52, June 20, 11 a.m., and your despatch No.
                            639, June 21. What steps, if any, has the Government of Honduras taken
                            to cooperate in making effective in the future the embargo against
                            contraband shipments to Honduras?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>